  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop the <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half, lengthways</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20-25 minutes or until golden</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1712133400601-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1712133400601-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1712133400601-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1712133400601-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1712133400601-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>free range</strong> <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to a clean chopping board</p><p>Slice through the thickest part of the chicken being careful not to cut all the way through to the other side and open it out like a book</p><p>Cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until you have an even thickness – this is your <strong>butterflied chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1712133406379-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1712133406379-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1712133406379-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1712133406379-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1712133406379-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate</p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>to a shallow bowl</p><p>Combine your<strong> panko breadcrumbs </strong>and <strong>nigella seeds</strong> with your <strong>curry powder</strong>, a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on a separate plate</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1712133411421-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1712133411421-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1712133411421-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1712133411421-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1712133411421-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Coat the <strong>butterflied chicken</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off any excess, then add to the <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and finally press into the <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>firmly to evenly coat all over – this is your <strong>breaded chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
